ride (third-person singular simple present rides, present participle riding, simple past rode or (obsolete) rade or (obsolete) rid, past participle ridden or (now colloquial and nonstandard) rode)

    1. (transitive, intransitive) To transport oneself by sitting on and directing a horse, later also a bicycle etc. [from 8th c., transitive usage from 9th c.]

2. (transitive, intransitive) To be transported in a vehicle; to travel as a passenger. [from 9th c., transitive usage from 19th c.]
3. (transitive, informal, chiefly US and South Africa) To transport (someone) in a vehicle. [from 17th c.]

I ride to work every day and park the bike outside the office.
